<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10791] RangeTombstones can be written after END_OF_ROW markers when streaming</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10791</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;SSTableWriter.appendFromStream&lt;/tt&gt; calls &lt;tt&gt;ColumnIndex.build&lt;/tt&gt; only after finishing the row and writing an &lt;tt&gt;END_OF_ROW&lt;/tt&gt; marker. After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7953&quot; title=&quot;RangeTombstones not merging during compaction&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7953&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7953&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the latter may still need to write tombstones.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
